<!-- SEO ARTICLE — unique to EN -->
<section class="article-section">
<div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">GUIDE</div>
<h2>How to sell on Ukrainian marketplaces without a local team</h2>
<div class="article-content">
<h3>Why Ukraine's marketplace economy matters</h3>
<p>Ukraine's e-commerce market exceeded $8 billion in 2024-2025, driven by rapid digitalization and a population of 37+ million active internet users. The dominant marketplaces &mdash; Rozetka (30M monthly visits), Prom.ua (40M), and OLX (60M) &mdash; collectively represent the largest online shopping ecosystem in Eastern Europe outside Russia. For international brands, this is an untapped market with high demand and relatively low competition from foreign sellers.</p>
<p>What makes Ukraine particularly attractive is the logistics infrastructure. Nova Poshta, the country's leading courier service, delivers to 30,000+ locations with next-day delivery in most cities. Combined with a fulfillment partner, you can reach Ukrainian consumers without setting up offices, hiring staff, or even visiting the country.</p>

<h3>The "no local entity" approach: how it works</h3>
<p>Traditionally, selling on Ukrainian marketplaces required a local FOP (sole proprietor) or LLC registration. This meant legal fees, a Ukrainian bank account, and weeks of paperwork. Modern fulfillment operators have changed this. You ship your inventory to a warehouse in Ukraine, and the operator handles everything: marketplace account management, order processing, packing, and delivery. For your initial market test, no local registration is needed &mdash; the operator can process shipments under their entity.</p>
<p>Once you validate the market and reach consistent volumes, you register a local entity. MTP Group works with legal partners who handle this process for foreign businesses, typically within 2-3 weeks. Sellers from Turkey, EU countries, the US, and UK are already using this approach.</p>

<h3>Choosing the right marketplace for your products</h3>
<p>Each Ukrainian marketplace serves a different audience and product category. Rozetka is the closest equivalent to Amazon &mdash; the broadest catalog with the highest trust among consumers. Prom.ua excels for niche and B2B products with over 100 million listings. Kasta dominates fashion and lifestyle, with 20,000+ daily orders. OLX, while primarily a classifieds platform, generates 60 million monthly visits and is particularly strong for electronics and household goods. Epicentr (20M monthly visits) offers low competition in home improvement and building materials.</p>
<p>The key advantage of a fulfillment partner is multi-marketplace selling: one warehouse, one inventory pool, orders from all platforms. MTP Group integrates with all major Ukrainian marketplaces via API, eliminating the risk of overselling and ensuring same-day dispatch regardless of where the order originates.</p>

<h3>What to expect: timeline and costs</h3>
<p>Getting started is faster than most international sellers expect. Day 1: sign a contract and configure API connections with your chosen marketplaces. Day 2: ship your goods to the warehouse near Kyiv (Boryspil area, close to the international airport). Day 3: the first orders are processed and handed to Nova Poshta. Total investment for a test launch: a minimum of 5,000 UAH (~$125) per month, covering fulfillment services, WMS access, packing materials, and shipping.</p>
<p>At scale, the economics become even more compelling. At 100+ orders per day, fulfillment costs approximately 20 UAH (~$0.50) per order. Compare this to setting up your own operation: warehouse lease ($400+/mo), staff ($500+/mo), software, insurance, and power backup. MTP Group's two warehouses near Kyiv (total 3,900 m&sup2;) are equipped with 3 generators and Starlink &mdash; zero downtime since 2022, even during the most severe power outages.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</Base>

